@startuml
title Tensor inference request - sequence view

actor Client
participant "REST route\n/v1/models/{model}/infer" as Route
participant BinaryTensorCodec as Protocol
participant InferenceService as Inference
participant RuntimeSupervisor as Runtime
participant "Worker process" as Worker
participant ModelRuntimeAdapter as Adapter
participant InferenceTelemetryRecorder as Telemetry
participant ObservabilityRecorder as Recorder
participant AutoRollbackMonitor as Rollback

Client -> Route: POST binary tensor request
Route -> Protocol: read_binary_tensor_request(request)
Protocol --> Route: header, payload
Route -> Inference: infer(model_name, header, payload)
Inference -> Runtime: get_loaded(model_name)
Runtime --> Inference: loaded model metadata
Inference -> Telemetry: start(model, version, request_id)
Inference -> Inference: validate_inputs()\nvalidate_output_names()
Inference -> Runtime: infer_tensors(model, inputs, payload, outputs)
Runtime -> Worker: IPC infer command + binary payload
Worker -> Adapter: run(output_names, input_feed)
Adapter --> Worker: output tensors
Worker --> Runtime: output headers + payload + timings
Runtime --> Inference: outputs, response payload, timings
Inference -> Telemetry: record_success(span, timings)
Telemetry -> Recorder: record timing events and metrics
Recorder -> Rollback: publish INFERENCE event
Rollback -> Rollback: evaluate policy when needed
Inference --> Route: response header, response payload
Route -> Protocol: make_binary_tensor_response(header, payload)
Protocol --> Route: octet-stream response
Route --> Client: 200 OK
@enduml
